Ingredients are consumed upon use, just like tools.

Be very cautious combining additional ingredients with *already framed* items; this often results in 'ruined frames' and value loss. Avoid cutting 'hard' items unless the other player's hint specifically suggests it, as this usually yields negative values. Don't overcomplicate your creations. If you have a solid positive score, it's often best to submit.

message: Focus on 'soft' ingredients. The most reliable path to a high score (45) is to first use 'scissors' on a 'soft' ingredient (e.g., paper, feather, leaf), then immediately use the 'frame' tool on that 'cut' soft item. Frame 'hard' items only if you've exhausted soft options, but they yield less value (20) than framed cut soft items. Don't overcomplicate!
